caption: Definitely a spot worth trying, the food is good and well prepared, the cost is reasonable and it is regularly neat in here. Keep it up.

At the moment  you step in that restaurant  team give you a pleasant feeling. Very warm waiters, it is a happy restaurant to hang out with friends and colleagues or with your date. Excellent  meals, qualified  chef de cuisine, decent  cost and attentive  service. Warmly recommended.

Stumbled upon Potbelly Sandwich Shop and am so glad we ended up here! The most refreshing, delicious food + friendly staff! It was the perfect day to sit on their outdoor patio & enjoy the sunshine with our food.

A sweet little ice cream shop that makes cute animal designs, my baby nieces absolutely love this place. The owner/owners daughter is also absolutely sweet, a relative of mine dropped his ice cream that he barely had eaten on the ground and they offered to replace it. Things like that make me appreciate small business. Thank you for a great evening of ice cream.

We recently ordered a family deal for curbside pickup and when we got home realized that the bag of cookies was missing. While not the end of the world, they went out of their way to make it up to us and when the computer system wouldn't let them refund us part of the money, they used door dash to get TWO bags to us for the inconvenience. Kadysha was especially friendly and motivated! You made my 3 kids VERY happy! We will be back due to the customer service!

All in all a good location for Potbelly. Service was very fast, efficient, and friendly. I did not know what I wanted, yet server was patient and did not make me feel rushed or like I was a burden.  I had the A Wreck, and it was by far the best served sandwich I have had at Potbelly. Ingredients were well balanced and the sandwich made well, without the leaks and mess that can happen.  Shake was very good too. Plenty of Oreo pieces, and the shake itself was on the thicker end of viscosity.

This might be the worst location of Potbelly in terms of service.  While it is fresh and new inside having opened less than a year ago the staff compared to busier stores in other locations is slow as molasses.  Once I was in here and the only available staff member was moping the floor while ignoring me.  Additionally in the evenings they have at times inexplicably not being able to make milkshakes.  The dining area is also a bit awakward and often is overly bright with sunlight in the evenings.  The food is the same as all locations and they staff aren't undfriendly but it's not a go to spot for me.
